title: For Sale:  **RARE** Sig Sauer P229 Equinox in 9mm
postcontent:
As the title says, this is a Sig Sauer P229.  As the title also says, this gun is rare.  Why is it rare?  The reason is because Sig never intended to make the P229 Equinox in 9mm.  From what I understand around #120 P229 9mm slides made there way to Sig's Custom Shop where the Equinox and other custom guns are finished.  Instead of scraping the slides that the Custom Shop had already performed work on, Sig decided to finish the guns.  With the limited quantity produced due to this mistake, these are few and far between in this configuration.

I'm not sure of exact round count but it's definitely very low (being a Sig and in as new condition, round count is irrelevant).  I have not fired this weapon as I have a couple other well-used Sigs.  Needless to say, the gun is in pristine condition with no signs of wear.  Comes with factory case, two 15 round magazine (one still sealed in wrapper), a Sig laser (not installed but shown in picture of the case) and Sig Nite sights on rear and TFO on front (this is standard on Equinox models).  I've also installed a nice stainless guide rod (the factory one is polymer and is included) and have purchased a Blackhawk CQC Serpa holster in carbon fiber finish (to my knowledge gun has never been holstered).

Price is $1,000 OBO (Will consider trade for a quality AR).  I'm in no way desperate to sell this weapon.  I'm located in the Lawrence/Maury County area and will not travel far.  TEXT 9three1-two1five-6eight5zero (serious inquiries only and no email please).  Buyer must provide proof of TN residency (TN HCP holders preferred).

title: For Sale/Trade:  For Sale/Trade: Lee-Enfield No5 MkI "Jungle Carbine"
postcontent:
Here is a great, and real, example of the Lee-Enfield No.5 MkI, commonly known as the Jungle Carbine. This is rifle was manufactured in 1946 at Royal Ordinance Factory Fazakerly, in Liverpool. Chambered in .303 British, these were the last major design change in the British production of the Lee-Enfield. They were produced from mid-1944 to 1947 and with only approximately 250,000 being made it is one of the rarest, and most collectible, of the Lee-Enfield models available. 
This particular rifle will come with a sling and the option of 90 rounds of commercial ammo. Only "blemish" on this rifle is where some young British soldier carved his initials into the stock, which I think is an interesting piece of history.

Rifle and sling - $550 obo
 Plus ammo - $600 obo
 Also willing to hear trade offers. Not interested in handguns or shotguns. 
Located in Linville, near Boone.

title: For Sale:  NEW - KEL-TEC KSG Bullpup 12Ga Pump Shotgun
postcontent:
Hoosier Armory:  KEL-TEC KSG 12Ga Shotgun

The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".

This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.

The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

Technical specs:

Caliber 	12 gauge 3”
Barrel length 	18.5"
Total capacity 	6+6+1
Weight empty 	6.9lbs
Weight loaded 	8.5lbs
Length 	26.1"
Height 	7"
MSRP 	$990.00

title: For Sale:  Custom Mosin
postcontent:
Custom built mosin with red star scope mount. I have a machine shop and make these mounts along with the muzzle break and bent bolt that is on this rifle. I have machined this 91/30 mosin to accept the scope mount and have threaded the barrel to accept the break which makes the recoil similar to a .223. The bolt has been cut off and I made a custom one that I welded on. I took 7 inches off the barrel. It has had a beautiful trigger job. Pull is about 2 pounds if I had to guess. postcontent: The R.P.D. was the first machine gun designed to fire the 7.62x39mm cartridge.  The R.P.D. platform has been issued by many countries including the Soviet Union, China, Egypt and former Eastern Bloc countries.  The R.P.D. was also used by the U.S. SOF in Vietnam.  DSA has modernized this battlefield benchmark with features such as a newly designed 7075T6 alloy lower and proprietary rail handguard.  With these new features you can outfit your R.P.D. system with any M16 style adjustable stock, giving the end user greater versatility. In addition, the DSA barrel is fluted and shortened.  This reduces weight and helps keep the barrel cool.  A very effective, proven design flashhider has also been added.  These features have reduced the R.P.D. weight by almost 2 pounds.  This one comes with an LMT adjustable stock.

postcontent:
I have a new in the box ATI LW FB 45 caliber. LW FB stands for LightWeight Fat Boy. Will hold 12 rounds plus 1. Called a fatboy because of the double stacked magazine, but really no wider than a single stack 1911. This 1911 is perfect for concealed carry as it is much smaller and much lighter than a regular full size 1911. Be over 21,have a FL drivers License and I will fill out a bill of sale. Not looking for trades. $625 cash firm.

FX45 Fatboy Lightweight .45ACP 3.2 Inch Flared Bull Barrel Blue Finish Combat Sights 12 Round

Designed on the 1911 platform with a wide-body frame. Ambidextrous safety. 3.2 inch flared bull barrel with blued finish. Carbon steel slide with front and rear serrations. Lowered and flared ejection port. Combat sights dovetailed into the slide. Dual recoil-spring system. extended slide catch. Beavertail grip safety. Skeletonized aluminum trigger. Lightweight alloy frame. Ultra-thin polymer grip panel.

Manufactuer: 	American Tactical Imports
Model: 	FX45 Fatboy Lightweight
Caliber: 	.45 ACP
Barrel Length:	3.2
Capacity:	12 + 1
Finish:	Blue
Hand Gun Web Model:	FX45

Overall length under seven inches, 5.5 inches high and only 1.33 inches at its widest point, the FX45 is easy to conceal even under light clothing. But it’s a true 1911 and has all of the excellent features John Moses Browning designed into his original pistol: single-action trigger, excellent ergonomics and well-placed controls that are easy to operate.
The machined steel slide has dual sets of grasping grooves, and the ejection port has been lowered and flared to ensure that spent cases get out of the way surely and quickly.
But the most modern feature is that it uses a bushing-less barrel with a flared muzzle section. Another departure from the original is a telescoping, dual-spring recoil system on a full-length guide rod. Both of these features ensure tight and consistent barrel/slide lockup for improved accuracy and functioning. It also greatly simplifies disassemble.
The low-profile rear sight has a large, easy-to-acquire square notch and is angled to prevent it from hanging up on clothing on the draw, and its rear face is serrated to reduce glare. The front is a square blade with a white dot insert.
The alloy frame pares the Fatboy LW’s unloaded weight to a mere 22 ounces, and the frame is undercut at the trigger guard to permit a high grip on the gun.
The ambidextrous thumb safety levers are smaller than normally seen on a 1911 but can still be operated positively. An extended beavertail grip safety with a palm swell provides superior handling while ameliorating recoil—a nice feature on a .45 pistol weighing so little. Aggressively checkered, polymer grip panels allow a secure grip.

I have a stainless steel Para 6.45 for sale. This was my primary carry gun for over a year. It has been an absolute joy. This is a super concealable .45 caliber power house with a match grade barrel. It is very accurate and has manageable recoil even though it is so small due to its all stainless steel construction. 

Why buy a used gun? Because you get great stuff with it!

This has been my primary carry gun. As such, you get a gun that is already broken in. It is already proven to run great. It comes with many extras that would otherwise cost you quite a bit of cash! The extras include:

This combination of holsters work great. The MTAC is one of the best CCW holsters that money can buy. It is very comfortable. The Serpa is a fantastic holster for open carry or the range. It is easy to use and has a retention clip to keep the gun in the holster. 

The stainless steel finish on this gun is ideal for those who actually want to carry the gun frequently. There is no coating that can wear off in time. It resists damage from sweat, oil, etc... This is an absolutely fantastic carry gun. 

Q: What is LDA?
A: For double action converts who prefer not to carry a “cocked and locked” 1911, PARA’s LDA (Light Double Action) system delivers 1911 performance from a double action fire control. Fire it and you’ll never pickup a standard double action pistol again.

What LDA means to me:
It is a super smooth and easy to operate double action only trigger. You do not need to carry "cocked and locked". The trigger feels like a well tuned revolver. Feel free to read up on this. Para Ordinance has created something very cool. 

In addition to the LDA, this gun has a grip safety and a manual safety. This gives you some added peace of mind when carrying the gun with you every day.
